'''Ajish''' is a common first name in [[Malayalam]], the regional language of the state of [[Kerala]] in [[India]]. Most commonly used by [[Christian]]s of [[Knanaya]] descent. The name Ajish also means in [[Hindi]] (another [[Indian language]]), ''[[Shiva]], Lord of the Goats''.

The Name Ajish is Varient of Ajesh or Ajeesh, which means "Not defeated by any one".  This is common name in Kerala. 

The acutal meaning of the name comes from Sanskrit.
Ajish is the combination of (a)ja + ish where 'aja' means unborn and 'ish' translates to Lord. So the word Ajish means 'Lord of the unborn'. Here unborn refers to beings like angels(easy name for all such other worldly beings) that are not born/created into the universe in the same sense as humans.

*'''Gender:''' Male
*'''Origin:''' Unknown
